# Implementation Plan: User & Patient APIs

We will implement the remaining CRUD and profile management API endpoints for **Users** and **Patients** in the application layer and API controllers layer.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Application Layer (Services)

We will create service interfaces and implementations to handle retrieving and modifying User account settings and Patient demographics details.

#### [NEW] [IUserService.cs & UserService.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Application/Services/UserService.cs)
Provides:
- `Task<UserDto> GetUserProfileAsync(Guid userId);`
- `Task ChangePasswordAsync(Guid userId, string currentPassword, string newPassword);`

#### [NEW] [IPatientService.cs & PatientService.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Application/Services/PatientService.cs)
Provides:
- `Task<PatientDto> GetPatientProfileAsync(Guid userId, Guid patientId);` (validates ownership/link in `UserPatients`)
- `Task<PatientDto> UpdatePatientProfileAsync(Guid userId, Guid patientId, PatientUpdateDto dto);` (validates access, updates name, DOB, blood group, emergency contact)

---

### 2. Application Layer (DTOs)

#### [NEW] [PatientUpdateDto.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Application/DTOs/PatientUpdateDto.cs)
Input fields for profile editing:
- `FirstName`, `LastName`, `MobileNo`, `Gender`, `DOB`, `BloodGroup`, `EmergencyContactName`, `EmergencyContactNumber`.

#### [NEW] [ChangePasswordDto.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Application/DTOs/ChangePasswordDto.cs)
Input fields for password changing:
- `CurrentPassword`, `NewPassword`.

---

### 3. API Layer (Controllers)

We will create the controllers to expose these services.

#### [NEW] [UsersController.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Controllers/UsersController.cs)
Exposes:
- `GET /api/users/profile` -> Gets current user profile (using header `X-User-Id`).
- `POST /api/users/change-password` -> Changes password.

#### [NEW] [PatientsController.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Controllers/PatientsController.cs)
Exposes:
- `GET /api/patients/{id}` -> Gets a specific patient profile.
- `PUT /api/patients/{id}` -> Updates patient demographics.

